hints_latex:
The definition of the derivative is

\begin{align*}
f'(x) = \lim_{h \to 0}\frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{h}
\end{align*}

statement_latex:
Let

\begin{align*}
f(x) = \frac{1}{x+1}
\end{align*} Find $f'(x)$ using the limit definition of
the derivative.

\emph{No marks will be given for using other methods in part (a).}
